  <p>4.<tab/>How many people have VWI sent abroad to work?</p>
   <list class="answerList2">
  <li><a id="a1">nearly 21,000</a></li>
  <li><a id="a2">21,000</a></li>
  <li><a id="a3">more than 21,000</a></li>
  </list>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>5.<tab/>Where do VWI volunteers come from?</p>
     <list class="answerList2">
  <li><a id="a4">The USA and Canada</a></li>
  <li><a id="a5">The USA and Europe</a></li>
  <li><a id="a6">Canada and Australia</a></li>
  </list>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>6.<tab/>How old is the oldest volunteer?</p>
       <list class="answerList2">
  <li><a id="a7">65</a></li>
  <li><a id="a8">66</a></li>
  <li><a id="a9">70</a></li>
  </list>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>7.<tab/>What are volunteers in Vietnam doing?</p>
       <list class="answerList2">
  <li><a id="a10">training teachers</a></li>
  <li><a id="a11">teaching English</a></li>
  <li><a id="a12">teaching primary school children</a></li>
  </list>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>8.<tab/>Where are volunteers in South Africa working?</p>
	<list class="answerList2">
  <li><a id="a13">in the cities</a></li>
  <li><a id="a14">in the countryside</a></li>
  <li><a id="a15">in both the cities and the countryside</a></li>
  </list>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>9.<tab/>Who are volunteers in Thailand training?</p>
         <list class="answerList2">
  <li><a id="a16">healthcare workers</a></li>
  <li><a id="a17">youth workers</a></li>
  <li><a id="a18">park workers</a></li>
  </list>
  
  </ol>
